# 15A. Popular Machine Learning Algorithms

Machine Learning algorithms are methods used to learn patterns from data.

Different algorithms solve different types of problems:
- prediction
- classification
- clustering
- recommendations
- image recognition
- NLP

---

## Linear Regression

Used for:
- predicting continuous values

Examples:
- house prices
- salary prediction
- stock prices

Formula:

```math
y = mx + b
```

---

## Logistic Regression

Used for:
- binary classification

Examples:
- spam detection
- fraud detection
- disease prediction

Outputs:
```text
0 or 1
Yes or No
```

---

## Decision Tree

Tree-like decision structure.

Example:

```text
Age > 18?
 ├── Yes → Eligible
 └── No → Not Eligible
```

Advantages:
- easy to understand
- interpretable

---

## Random Forest

Collection of multiple decision trees.

Concept:

```text
Many Trees → Combined Decision
```

Advantages:
- better accuracy
- reduces overfitting

Very popular for:
- business/tabular data

---

## Support Vector Machine (SVM)

Used for:
- classification problems

Concept:
- finds best boundary between classes

Good for:
- smaller datasets
- high-dimensional data

---

## K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

Distance-based algorithm.

Concept:

```text
Nearby points belong to similar categories
```

Applications:
- recommendations
- pattern matching

---

## Naive Bayes

Probability-based algorithm.

Commonly used for:
- spam filtering
- sentiment analysis
- text classification

Advantages:
- very fast
- efficient for text data

---

## K-Means Clustering

Unsupervised learning algorithm.

Purpose:
- group similar data points

Applications:
- customer segmentation
- user behavior grouping

---

## PCA (Principal Component Analysis)

Used for:
- dimensionality reduction

Example:

```text
100 Features → 10 Important Features
```

Purpose:
- reduce complexity
- improve performance

---

## Gradient Boosting

Ensemble learning method.

Popular implementations:
- XGBoost
- LightGBM
- CatBoost

Known for:
- very high accuracy
- winning ML competitions

---

## XGBoost

One of the most widely used ML algorithms.

Applications:
- fraud detection
- ranking systems
- recommendation systems

Advantages:
- fast
- scalable
- highly accurate

---

## Neural Networks

Inspired by human brain neurons.

Structure:
- Input Layer
- Hidden Layers
- Output Layer

Applications:
- images
- NLP
- speech recognition

---

## Deep Learning

Uses very large neural networks.

Applications:
- ChatGPT
- face recognition
- autonomous vehicles

Frameworks:
- TensorFlow
- PyTorch

---

## Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN)

Specialized for image processing.

Applications:
- image classification
- object detection
- medical imaging

---

## Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN)

Designed for sequential data.

Applications:
- speech recognition
- time series
- language modeling

---

## LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)

Improved version of RNN.

Better for:
- long sequences
- remembering past information

Applications:
- NLP
- stock prediction
- speech systems

---

## Transformers

Modern deep learning architecture.

Used in:
- ChatGPT
- Gemini
- Claude
- translation systems

Advantages:
- parallel processing
- context understanding
- scalability

Most important architecture in modern AI.

---

## Reinforcement Learning Algorithms

Learning using rewards and penalties.

Applications:
- robotics
- game AI
- autonomous systems

Popular methods:
- Q-Learning
- Deep Q Networks (DQN)

---

## Recommendation Algorithms

Used by:
- Netflix
- Amazon
- YouTube

Methods:
- Collaborative Filtering
- Matrix Factorization

---

